messages.content: what are the biggest painpoints customers face when they are interested in kununu

As of July 16, 2025, customers interested in using Kununu, whether they are job seekers, employees, or employers, face several pain points. These issues primarily revolve around the authenticity and management of reviews, legal challenges, and the need for proactive reputation management.

One of the most significant pain points is the **difficulty in managing negative and potentially unfair reviews** [lhr-law](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [lhr-law](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1]. Companies regularly encounter legal disputes due to anonymous reviews containing damaging or personally motivated claims [lhr-law](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [lhr-law](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1]. Approximately 10% of reviews attract complaints, often concerning slander and false statements [aimgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2]. Businesses in sales and direct marketing are particularly vulnerable, as negative reviews can impact customer acquisition and team motivation [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3]. Responding emotionally to these reviews is often a mistake [anwalt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4). The impact of negative reviews is substantial, with almost half of potential applicants deciding against a potential employer due to negative online feedback [activelaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5).

Another major concern is the **authenticity of reviews**. There are concerns about companies creating "fake-positive" reviews to manipulate their ratings [omr](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6), and users report companies posting fake positive reviews to bury negative ones [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0]. Some users suggest Kununu gets paid to remove negative reviews [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0], and there are claims that companies pressure employees to leave positive reviews [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0) [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1]. Kununu states they investigate suspicious reviews [omr](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6) and employs staff to investigate complaints, focusing on slander and false statements [aimgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [aimgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1]. They also demand evidence when employers question a review's authenticity [itmedialaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-7) and contact review authors, requesting anonymized proof of their employment [goldberg](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-5) [buse](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-8).

**Legal challenges** also present a pain point. Companies may need to take legal action to remove unlawful statements [activelaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5]. A court ruling in Hamburg has challenged the anonymity of reviewers, potentially requiring Kununu to disclose reviewer names if employers doubt the authenticity of negative reviews [mainwerk-legal](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2) [itmedialaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [goldberg](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4] [goldberg](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-5) [mainwerk-legal](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-6) [itmedialaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-7]. Kununu is reportedly taking legal action against this decision [itmedialaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [aimgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1) [itmedialaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-7]. To challenge a review, employers should point out the legal violation and/or violation of guidelines to Kununu and request deletion [anwalt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4].

The **need for proactive reputation management** is also crucial [activelaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5]. Companies should monitor what is being written about them on review portals [activelaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5]. Responding objectively to criticism can signal that the company takes feedback seriously [activelaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5].

Other issues include typical negative reviews mentioning below-average salaries, lack of interest in structural employee leasing, and a lack of humanity from the employer [anwalt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4]. Kununu is working to increase its overall brand awareness [omr](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6).

Kununu aims to improve the job market by promoting transparency [slashdot](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-15) [slashdot](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-16) and offers solutions to help companies improve employee engagement and gather feedback, such as kununu engage [g2](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [saasworthy](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8]. They also highlight companies with good reviews through "Top Company" awards [swarmit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-9) [makandra](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10) [tlc](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-11) [kununu](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-12) [kingnature](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-10) [isys](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-11) [igp-powder](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-12) [makandra](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-13].

Okay, I will conduct Google Searches to gather information on "kununu customer pain points 2025" and synthesize it into a verifiable text artifact.
Based on the search results, here's a synthesis of potential pain points for Kununu customers in 2025:

**1. Difficulty Managing Negative and Potentially Unfair Reviews:**

*   Companies regularly face legal disputes due to anonymous reviews on Kununu that contain damaging or personally motivated claims [lhr-law](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [lhr-law](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1).
*   A significant percentage of reviews (around 10%) attract complaints, often focusing on perceived slander and false statements [aimgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2).
*   Companies in sales and direct marketing may be particularly vulnerable to negative Kununu reviews that impact customer acquisition and team motivation [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3).
*   Responding emotionally to negative reviews can be a mistake [anwalt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4).
*   Negative reviews can significantly impact potential applicants, with almost half deciding against a potential employer due to negative online reviews [activelaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5).

**2. Concerns About Review Authenticity:**

*   There are concerns about "fake-positive" reviews, where companies create their own positive feedback [omr](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6). Kununu states they investigate suspicious reviews [omr](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6).
*   A court case in Germany (though subject to ongoing appeals) highlights the debate around anonymity, with some arguing employers should be able to identify reviewers to verify their relationship with the company [aimgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2).
*   The Higher Regional Court of Hamburg ruled that Kununu must disclose the real names of users in order to check the authenticity of reviews [anwalt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4). Kununu plans to have the decision reviewed [anwalt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4).

**3. Legal Challenges and the Burden of Proof:**

*   Companies may need to take legal action to remove unlawful statements [activelaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5).
*   To challenge a review, employers should point out the legal violation and/or violation of guidelines to Kununu and request deletion [anwalt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4).
*   Reviews containing untrue statements of fact, formal insults, or abusive criticism can be challenged [activelaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5).
*   A German court ruled that a company is entitled to information about the authors of negative Kununu reviews, marking progress against anonymous and unlawful reviews [lhr-law](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [lhr-law](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).

**4. Need for Proactive Reputation Management:**

*   Companies should monitor what is being written about them on review portals [activelaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5).
*   Responding objectively to criticism can signal that the company takes feedback seriously [activelaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5).
*   Kununu's CEO emphasizes the importance of transparency, acknowledging that criticism is part of creating a balanced platform [omr](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6).

**5. Other Potential Issues:**

*   Some typical negative reviews on Kununu in 2025 include mentions of below-average salaries, lack of interest in structural employee leasing, and a lack of humanity from the employer [anwalt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4).
*   Kununu is working to increase its overall brand awareness [omr](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6).

It is important to note that Kununu also offers solutions to help companies improve employee engagement and gather feedback, such as kununu engage [g2](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [saasworthy](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8). They also highlight companies with good reviews through "Top Company" awards [swarmit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-9) [makandra](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10) [tlc](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-11) [kununu](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-12).

As of July 16, 2025, information regarding the specific methodologies and criteria Kununu uses to investigate and address fake or manipulated reviews is limited. However, some insights can be gathered from recent news and discussions:

**General Procedures and Detection Mechanisms:**

*   **Standardized Review Process:** Kununu emphasizes a standardized review process to prevent fake reviews and abuse [kingnature](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0).
*   **Verification of Employment:** Kununu has been known to request proof from reviewers that they worked at the company they are reviewing, sometimes asking for payslips or employment contracts [aimgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1) [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-2).
*   **IP Address Monitoring:** There are suggestions that review platforms should monitor IP addresses to detect suspicious patterns [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-3).
*   **Analysis of Review Content:** Analytical tools and AI can be used to detect suspicious patterns in review content, such as overly positive or negative language, lack of specific details, or repetitive language [digitalsociety](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-4).
*   **Behavioral Analysis:** Unusual reviewer activity, such as posting too frequently or fixating on certain products, can be identified through behavioral analysis [digitalsociety](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-4).

**Legal Considerations and Court Rulings:**

*   **Disclosure of Reviewer Identity:** A ruling by the Higher Regional Court of Hamburg stated that Kununu might have to disclose the names of reviewers if employers doubt the authenticity of reviews [goldberg](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-5) [mainwerk-legal](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-6) [itmedialaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-7). *   **Employer's Right to Know:** The court ruled that employers should be able to ascertain if they ever had a relationship with the person posting a negative review [aimgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1).
*   **Federal Court of Justice Requirements:** German's Federal Court of Justice states that review services must investigate potentially false comments by acquiring proof that the user works or has worked for the reviewed company [aimgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1).
*   **Kununu's Response:** Kununu has expressed disagreement with court decisions that require them to reveal reviewer identities and has taken legal action against such rulings [aimgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1) [itmedialaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-7).

**Kununu's Actions:**

*   **Investigation of Complaints:** Kununu employs a team to investigate complaints, particularly those concerning slander and false statements [aimgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1).
*   **Demanding Evidence:** When employers question a review's authenticity, Kununu demands evidence [itmedialaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-7).

**Challenges and Considerations:**

*   **Balancing Anonymity and Authenticity:** Kununu faces the challenge of balancing user privacy with the need to ensure review authenticity [itmedialaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-7).
*   **Adapting Policies:** Review platforms need to adapt their policies and procedures to ensure both privacy and legality [itmedialaw](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-7).
*   **Potential for Legal Consequences:** Reviewers may face legal consequences for untruthful reviews [mainwerk-legal](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-6).
*   **Difficulties in Appeasing Employers:** It's becoming increasingly difficult for job sites to appease both candidates/reviewers and employers [aimgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1).
